    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1586"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1586">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 723.2515/272.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to Chile</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1912</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs has given out statement to the effect that an
                    agreement has been effected by telegraph with Peru to reestablish diplomatic
                    relations and fixing precise terms of settlement <pb facs="1329" n="1225"
                        xml:id="pg_1225"/> of the Tacna Arica question. Council of State will be
                    held today and if they approve the bases of settlement will be submitted to
                    Congress at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
